        <h2>Getting started with Meal Tracking</h2>

        <h2>What is Meal Prepping?</h2>
        <br />
        <p>
            Meal Prepping is the simple act of planning your meals ahead of time, then prepping the food (making the recipes) for the week ahead.
            Many people have the assumption that meal planning is tough and full of kitchen labor.
            On top of it, the internet is full of blogs and "experts" on meal prepping. It can be exhausting
            trying to find the perfect plan for your lifestyle AND also your budget. Especially trying
            to find food that you will ENJOY!

            Though,Meal prepping has been touted as a nutrition go-to by many fitness experts and nutritionists.
            AND if done right, meal prepping can not only help you <strong>SAVE MONEY</strong>, but it can also be the
            key to <strong>WEIGHT LOSS</strong>.
        </p>

        <h2>Meal Prepping Benefits</h2>
        <br />
        <p>

            The benefits of meal prepping range from lower food cost to time spent in the kitchen to lower stress
            and successful weight loss. If you take control of your diet and the foods you are eating, you are sure to be successful.
            Having a meal plan and food on hand will reduce your guilty hunger based decisions. When we are tired and hungry, we
            tend to grab the quickest thing, which most of the time is not healthy.

            If you want to save money, your sanity and live a healthy lifestyle, meal prepping is definitely for you!
        </p>

        <br />
        <br />

